FIRST AMENDED AND RESTATED MASTER INTERCONNECTION SERVICES
AGREEMENT
This First Amended and Restated Master Interconnection Services Agreement (this
“MISA”), dated as of December 3, 2021 (the “Execution Date”), is entered into by and among
Assembly Solar, LLC (“Interconnection Provider”), and each Person that becomes a party hereto
by execution and delivery of a Service Agreement in the form of Exhibit D (such Persons, the
“Users”). With respect to each User, this MISA, any exhibits, schedules and appendices hereto,
together with such User’s Service Agreement, shall be referred to as the “Agreement” between
such User and the other parties hereto.
RECITALS
A. Each User owns and operates a Project (as defined below)
B. Interconnection Provider is a party to that certain Generator Interconnection
Agreement made and entered into as of November 11, 2019, as amended and restated in its
entirety on May 29, 2020 (collectively, the “Interconnection Agreement”) by and among
Interconnection Provider as the Interconnection Customer, Michigan Electric Transmission
Company, (“Transmission Owner”) and the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc.
(“MISO” or “Transmission Provider”).
C. The Interconnection Agreement grants the Interconnection Customer certain
rights as set forth in the Interconnection Agreement (“Interconnection Rights”).
D. Interconnection Provider owns, or has certain rights to use, the Interconnection
Facilities (as defined below).
E. User desires to utilize the Interconnection Rights and Interconnection Facilities in
order to deliver electricity from its Project to the Point of Interconnection (as defined below).
F. Interconnection Provider and each User desire to set forth their respective rights
and obligations with respect to the Projects and the Interconnection Rights and Interconnection
Facilities.
G. The original Master Interconnection Services Agreement, dated as of December
27, 2019 (the “Original Agreement”) was accepted for filing by FERC June 23, 2020 in Docket
ER20-1693) and has been joined by the following Users: (i) AS1 (Certificate of Concurrence
and Service Agreement, dated as of December 27, 2019 and accepted for filing by FERC July
10, 2020, Docket ER20-1998-000), (ii) AS2 (Certificate of Concurrence and Service Agreement,
dated as of December 27, 2019 and accepted for filing by FERC May 5, Docket ER21-1378-
000), (iii) AS3 (Certificate of Concurrence and Service Agreement, dated as of November 13,
2020 and accepted for filing by FERC August 11, 2021, Docket ER21-1917-001).
E. The Interconnection Party and current Users now wish to amend and restate the
Original Agreement as of the Execution Date on the terms and conditions set forth below, with
this MISA becoming effective upon the date designated by FERC; Interconnection Party will
submit this MISA to FERC and each User shall submit a new Certificate of Concurrence.

contained herein, and for other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and adequacy of
which are hereby acknowledged by the Parties, the Parties agree as follows:
1. DEFINITIONS AND INTERPRETATION
1.1 Definitions. Unless otherwise noted, capitalized terms not defined in the body of
this Agreement have the following meanings.
“Affiliate” means, with respect to any Party, any Person directly or indirectly controlling,
controlled by or under common control with such Party. The term “control” and correlative
terms includes the possession, directly or indirectly and whether acting alone or in conjunction
with others, of the authority to direct or cause the direction of the management or policies of a
Person, whether through the ownership of voting securities, by contract, or otherwise.

“AS1” means Assembly Solar I, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company.
“AS2” means Assembly Solar II, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company.
“AS3” means Assembly Solar III, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company.
“Capacity Log” means the form attached hereto as Exhibit B, showing the Reserved
Capacity and generally applicable Cost Percentage (i.e, for expenses not otherwise specified by a
particular Cost Percentage on Exhibit C) of each User.
“Casualty Event” means an event that causes all or a portion of the Interconnection
Facilities or Perimeter Fencing to be damaged, destroyed or rendered unfit for normal use for any
reason whatsoever.
“Condemnation Event” means any compulsory transfer or taking or transfer under threat
of compulsory transfer or taking of all or a material part of the Interconnection Facilities or
Perimeter Fencing by any Governmental Authority or entity acting under power of eminent
domain.
“Confidential Information,” with respect to a given Disclosing Party and the respective
Receiving Party, means, collectively and individually, all data, materials and information
(including software, data, technology, know-how, trade secrets, processes, ideas, inventions
(whether patentable or not), prototypes, schematics, design plans, drawings, pricing information,
customer and service provider lists, business arrangements, business information, financial
information, financial results, technical information, analyses, forecasts, compilations, studies,
contracts, agreements, and planning or strategy information) provided by or on behalf of a Party
(each Party in such capacity, a “Disclosing Party”) to the other Party (each Party in such
capacity, a “Receiving Party”) or the Receiving Party’s Representatives, or to which the
Receiving Party or the Receiving Party’s Representatives are given access by or on behalf of the
Disclosing Party, whether verbally or in written or electronic form, related to the Disclosing
Party, any Project, the Interconnection Facilities, the Perimeter Fencing, the Managed Assets, the

Confidential Information under this Agreement does not include any information that: (A) the
Receiving Party can demonstrate is now publicly available, or that later becomes publicly
available through no action by the Receiving Party or the Receiving Party’s Representatives in
violation of this Agreement; (B) the Receiving Party can demonstrate is already in the possession
of the Receiving Party or the Receiving Party’s Representatives and is not subject to a
confidentiality or fiduciary obligation at the time of the information’s disclosure under this
Agreement; (C) the Receiving Party can demonstrate is lawfully received from any source other
than the Disclosing Party or the Disclosing Party’s Representatives under circumstances not
involving, to the Receiving Party’s knowledge, a breach of any fiduciary or confidentiality
obligation; or (D) the Receiving Party can demonstrate is independently developed by or for the
Receiving Party or the Receiving Party’s Representatives without reference to, or the use of, any
portion of the Confidential Information.
“Consent of the Users” means the written consent of Users that hold more than fifty
percent (50%) of the aggregate Reserved Capacity of all Users whose Projects are connected and
Energized. With respect to decisions affecting a Managed Asset, only Users with an ownership
interest in such asset shall be considered in determining whether the Consent of the Users has
occurred.
“Cost Percentage” is a fraction, with respect to a User, where (a) the numerator is the
Nameplate Capacity of such User’s Project or Projects with respect to each segment of the
Interconnection Facilities, the Perimeter Fencing or the Managed Assets and (b) the denominator
is the Nameplate Capacity of all of the current Users’ Projects utilizing that segment of the
Interconnection Facilities, the Perimeter Fencing or the Managed Assets. Any Person becoming a
New User under this Agreement will be assigned a Cost Percentage with respect to each segment
of the Interconnection Facilities, the Perimeter Fencing and the Managed Assets based on an
adjusted aggregated capacity that utilizes each segment of the Interconnection Facilities, the
Perimeter Fencing and Managed Assets that includes the New User’s Project Nameplate
Capacity. Upon the admittance of a New User, the Cost Percentage of all of the existing Users
will be similarly adjusted by the new denominator (if applicable) representing the new
aggregated Nameplate Capacity of all Users’ Projects. The Cost Percentage shall be determined
and applied with respect to those segments of the Interconnection Facilities, the Perimeter
Fencing and Managed Assets as specified in Exhibit C to this Agreement, as such exhibit may be
updated by notice to the Users from time to time.
“CUP” means that certain Special Land Use Permit and Final Site Plan, PSUP18-07 and
PSUP18-08, in favor of applicant Assembly Solar, LLC, and approved by the Shiawassee
County Planning Commission on February 5, 2019.
“Default Rate” means a rate per annum equal to the lesser of (a) a varying rate per annum
equal to the sum of (i) the three (3) month LIBOR as published in The Wall Street Journal, with
adjustments in that varying rate to be made on the same date as any change in that rate is so
published, plus (ii) two percent (2%) per annum, and (b) the maximum rate permitted by Law. If
LIBOR is no longer available, then the Default Rate shall utilize a successor rate or reasonable
replacement rate, as selected by Interconnection Provider.

Insurance Requirements
At all times during the term of this Agreement, each Party shall maintain the following minimum
insurance:
i) Commercial general liability insurance on an occurrence basis and
insuring against claims on account of loss of life, bodily injury or property damage and
having a combined single limit of coverage for bodily injury and property damage in the
amount of not less than $5,000,000 per occurrence and $5,000,000 in the annual
aggregate. Such policy shall further provide for blanket contractual liability, products
and completed operations, explosion and collapse hazard coverage, broad-form property
damage and personal liability coverage.
ii) If applicable, Business automobile insurance with a minimum limit of
$1,000,000 each accident with respect to bodily injury, death and property damage
combined and including coverage for all owned, non-owned and hired autos.
iii) Worker’s compensation insurance with statutory limits and employer’s
liability coverage with limits of $5,000,000 each accident, bodily injury for each
employee by disease and policy limit by disease, if applicable.
The limits for the commercial general liability, business automobile and worker’s
compensation/employer’s liability coverages required by subparagraphs (i), (ii) and (iii) in
paragraph (a) above, respectively, may be provided as a single limit or achieved by any
combination of primary and umbrella or excess liability limits, provided that the umbrella policy
meets all the terms and conditions contained herein, and is provided on a follow-form basis.
At all times during the term of this Agreement, the Interconnection Provider shall maintain all
risk property insurance covering the physical loss or damage (including testing and
commissioning) including physical loss or damage related to the following:
i) Lightning, strike, riot, vandalism, sabotage, aircraft collision, theft and
malicious mischief;
ii) Earthquake and flood with limits and deductibles approved by each User
and Financing Parties; and
iii) Hail, wind and named windstorm with limit and deductible approved by
each User and any Financing Parties;
iv) Mechanical and electrical breakdown including coverage for resulting or
ensuing damage arising out of design error, faulty materials or faulty workmanship;
v) Owned transmission lines, pylons and electrical switchgear subject to a
sublimit of no less than full replacement value;

to non-owned Interconnection Facilities up to the first non-owned substation, on broadest

Limits of policy will be at least the full replacement value of the covered property, subject to
applicable sub-limits. Policy shall provide for claims to be paid based upon replacement cost of
the lost or damaged property without deduction for depreciation. The policy shall have a
deductible of no greater than $250,000 per occurrence, with the exception of hail and tornado
which shall have a deductible of no greater than 5% per occurrence of damage of loss with a
minimum $250,000. Interconnection Provider shall be responsible for all deductibles under such
policy.
All such insurance shall be provided by an insurance company or companies qualified to do
business in the State of Michigan financially capable of fulfilling the requirements of such
policies, and having an A.M. Best rating of “A- / IX” or in one of the two highest rating
categories by Moody’s and S&P. Each policy shall be of such form and contain such provisions
as are generally considered standard for the type of insurance involved.
The insurance coverage required herein shall be provided without liability on the part of any
Party for premiums owed by the other. Further, each Party agrees that at any point when any
other Party, its agents, its employees, contractors or consultants shall enter its property to

maintained by that Party and all required additional-insured endorsements, and, within thirty (30)
days prior to the expiration of any such insurance, other certificates evidencing the renewal of
such insurance. Each Party shall provide the other with thirty (30) days’ written notice of
cancellation and (10) days’ notice for non-payment of premiums.
